    {
        "content": "<p>It's equivalent to presheaves over the discrete category generated by X but that includes a lot of trivial data and some constructions have simpler definitions (like if X is a monoid that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mtext>Set</mtext><mi>X</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\textrm{Set}^X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9146em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord textrm\">Set</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.9146em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.1362em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is a monoidal category is much simpler than the Day convolution which involves coends)</p>",
        "id": 524806462,
        "sender_full_name": "Max New",
        "timestamp": 1750299773
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's a namespace <code>FunctorToType</code>, and there's a few things about presheaves, but to my knowledge that's about it.</p>",
